name: RECTANGLE PURSE Blue Eucalypt
description:
These rectangle purses make great little gifts and are perfect for your coins, phone or makeup.

Made from the fabric offcuts of larger bags, means zero waste.

• Genuine leather and 100% cotton
• Dimensions: 17(w) x 11(h)cm
• Hand printed with water based ink
• High quality YKK zips

* Position of print and purse size may vary slightly due to handmade process.

About this print: 
In this print, perched amongst Eucalypt leaves, is the White-Browed Scrubwren. This little guy is very shy but has a loud alarm call. You’ll find him eating insects along coastal areas of Australia and, interestingly all group members help to feed and rear the young, not just the parents.

name: RECTANGLE PURSE Black Cockatoo
description:
These rectangle purses make great little gifts and are perfect for your coins, phone or makeup.

Made from the fabric offcuts of larger bags, means zero waste.

• 100% organic cotton/hemp
• Genuine leather
• Dimensions: 17(w) x 11(h)cm
• Hand printed with water based ink
• High quality YKK zips

About the print:
Found no where else in the world, there are five species of black cockatoos in Australia – red-tailed, glossy, yellow-tailed, Carnaby’s and Baudin’s. Interestingly, Black cockatoos can live to be more than 50 years old. Here I have created a watercolour to represent them where I usually see them - amidst the tops of trees looking down on me with suspicion.

I love that lino-cut prints express intimate, human qualities in their imperfections reflecting their truly handmade beginnings.
